
<section xml:id="conditionalProbabilitySection">
  <title>Conditional probability</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      <index><main>data</main><sub>family_college</sub></index>
    </p>

    <p>
      The <c>family_college</c> data set contains a sample of 792 cases with two variables, <c>teen</c> and <c>parents</c>, and is summarized in <xref ref="contTableOfParStCollege">Table</xref>.<fn>A simulated data set based on real population summaries at MISSINGoiRedirect.</fn> The <c>teen</c> variable is either <c>college</c> or <c>not</c>, where the teenager is labeled as <c>college</c> if she went to college immediately after high school. The <c>parents</c> variable takes the value <c>degree</c> if at least one parent of the teenager completed a college degree.
    </p>

